    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="essay">
                <p><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>There were sweet sounds mingled with my dreaming<lb/>
                    and a thousand airy orbs of many coloured light floated<lb/>
                    around me, and a bright shower of silvery light fell upon me<lb/>
                    <pb facs="MSVIII82r"/>
                    <fw type="pageNum" place="top-right"><handShift new="#HANDWGC" medium="pencil"/>82</fw>
                    <handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>and I started, and looked up. It was cold, very cold<lb/>
                    and the crisp ice of the July morning shot its long<lb/>
                    fleecy crystals over the narrow window <space quantity="3" unit="chars"/>Break the veil<lb/>
                    away, and look out. There was no sunshine, the <orgName corresp="#AUGUSTINIANS">Augus&#x2010;<lb/>
                    tines</orgName> <del rend="strikethrough">of</del> have not a perfectly clear day twelve times in<lb/>
                    the year, yet the landscape was dazzling white with<lb/>
                    broad sheets of pure summer snow that clung to the<lb/>
                    rugged crags as if it loved them, and grew broader, and<lb/>
                    deeper and whiter as it climbed up into the cloud, <del rend="strikethrough">and</del><lb/>
                    <del rend="strikethrough">th</del> through which it shone like a flood of sunlight<lb/>
                    while the tall steep <del rend="strikethrough">g</del> crags that rose forth of it, past<lb/>
                    away into the grey mist.<lb/></p>
            </div>
